\par }{\insrsid3627952 
\par }{\insrsid7090824\charrsid536913 So, we have three main causes of the
 heating up of the planet. Now, just to repeat: impacts from the objects outside the planet, radioactive decay of the elements inside, and heating due to pressure caused by gravity. So over the course of a billion years, all these things eventually pushed
 
up the heat until temperatures were hot enough to melt iron and other rocks. Now, as you know, the Earth is composed of a variety of different types of materials - and so these rocks and minerals have different densities. So, that means that heavier, the 
